Hello, I just completed the stripe verification to get access to my funds and the app will not allow me to access them.
I had to complete it in a separate browser on my phone

Thank you for your patience and for letting us know you completed Stripe verification via a separate browser. Here are some possible reasons you may not yet have access to your funds: Manual review required: Payouts are sometimes placed under manual review for account security or if risk control alerts are triggered. This can happen for new sellers or when completing verification in an unusual way (like through a separate browser). Manual reviews usually finish within 24 hours, and you will be notified once your payout is approved.⁠ ⁠​ Recent rollout of verification: Our new Stripe identity verification process is still being improved. Sellers must first pass both phone and Stripe identity verification before payout. If either is incomplete or not synced correctly (which can occasionally happen if done on mobile), it might delay access.⁠ ⁠⁠ ⁠​ Stripe payout processing time: Standard Stripe (ACH/bank) payouts can take 1-3 business days once they're released, and there may also be delays on holidays or weekends.⁠
Okay thank you! I was able to get it processed 👍
Always happy to help!
Please feel free to contact us if you need further assistance.

As for your comments about refunds and the pending balance, you are absolutely right. If your funds are stuck in pending, you are not expected to link a card or process refunds out of pocket. It makes sense to wait until funds are in your available balance, and we fully support that approach. You have every right to protect your finances, especially if you’re dealing with high pending amounts. We're working on improvements to how quickly those funds move from pending to available, and I know that’s a bigger system issue that affects many sellers, not just you. We also understand how exhausting it is to be constantly asked about refunds and cancellations, especially when it's the same problematic buyers again and again. You're not alone in this, and we're actively working to improve how we handle these kinds of patterns so they stop landing on your shoulders. Again, thank you for speaking up and for being so clear about what you're experiencing. Your feedback helps us make things better, and we really do want to support you in running your shop smoothly and fairly. If there's anything else you need or if you'd like us to flag any future buyer interactions ahead of time, we’re here to help. 💚

Here’s an update on your questions: Searching by Customer Name (on Laptop/Seller Hub): Currently, desktop (Seller Hub) search features are limited. Most seller search experiences only support searching by username (not full customer names) or order numbers, and this has been flagged as a pain point for sellers who need to quickly locate orders for tasks like inputting tracking numbers⁠⁠. An improved and more flexible order search/filtering system—including search by user/customer—is actively in progress for Seller Hub. This would allow searching for orders with different criteria such as username, order ID, product name, or even notes, but searching by full customer name (not just username) is a requested feature, not yet released⁠⁠. The lack of a reliable name-based search is a known workflow issue currently being worked on, but as of now, there’s no direct way to search by customer full name on desktop. Local Pickup Customers Filter: There is no dedicated tab or filter for local pickup customers at this time, but community/user feedback (including yours) has suggested adding tabs or filters specifically for “local pickup” to make managing those orders easier. This request is noted and part of ongoing product feedback, but no such feature has been released yet⁠. Coupon Deadlines for Events (e.g., Memorial Day): Coupon distribution for special events is usually managed with strict advance deadlines. This helps the system batch, verify, and properly fund all coupons across sellers, buyers, and events. Unfortunately, this means that if a message about the event or coupon is not seen in time (e.g., due to catching up with messages late), the deadline may already have passed. This policy is not uncommon in multi-seller live events, but your feedback on the timeline is valid and has been shared by other sellers as well.
